ss="description Description-module__T5pcGa__root Description-module__T5pcGa__clamped"><div class="Description-module__T5pcGa__wrapper"><p data-cy="document-description">Kidney stones are hard masses that form from crystals in the urine within the kidneys or urinary tract. They can cause severe pain when passing through the urinary system. Risk factors include dehydration, a family history of kidney stones, and medical conditions that disrupt the balance of salts in urine. Symptoms include intense pain in the back or side and blood in the urine. Diagnosis is usually done through CT scan or ultrasound. Small stones often pass on their own but larger ones may require lithotripsy to break them up for easier passing or surgical removal. Drinking plenty of water and managing diet are important for prevention.</p><!--&--><div class="CategoryLinks-module__FTe7aG__root"><a class="link link-module__Gim9xG__root link-module__Gim9xG__primary weight-medium link-module__Gim9xG__medium link-module__Gim9xG__underline" aria-label="View the featured presentations, documents and infographics in the Health &amp; Medicine Category" href="/category/health-medicine">Health &amp; Medicine</a><span class="text Text-module__DjdFRa__root weight-regular Text-module__DjdFRa__medium">◦</span></div><!--/&--></div><!--&--><button type="button" class="button Button-module__4HgN-q__root Button-module__4HgN-q__primary Button-module__4HgN-q__text Button-module__4HgN-q__medium Description-module__T5pcGa__readMore" aria-label="Read more" data-cy="read-more-button"><span><span class="Button-module__4HgN-q__spinnerSlide"><svg class="spinner" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 50 50" width="16" height="16" fill="currentColor" data-dd-excluded-activity-mutations="true"><path d="M43.935,25.145c0-10.318-8.364-18.683-18.683-18.683c-10.318,0-18.683,8.365-18.683,18.683h4.068c0-8.071,6.543-14.615,14.615-14.615c8.072,0,14.615,6.543,14.615,14.615H43.935z"><animateTransform attributeType="xml" attribute