ns may distort pelvic bones, such as rickets or a pelvic fracture, and lead to CPD. This file contains definition, causes , risk factors, clinical features, diagnostic test, management,  complications. ","tags":["all nursing and medical stu.","all nursing students","research"],"url":"https://www.slideshare.net/slideshow/cpd-pdf-by-preeti-kulshrestha-obstetrics-and-gynecology/288013029","userLogin":"PreetiKulshreshtha3","userName":"Preeti Kulshreshtha","viewCount":19},{"algorithmId":"4","displayTitle":"TKR[total knee replacement]-SURGERY OF THE CENTURY DR MOHAMED ASHRAF alleppey...","extension":"pptx","isSavedByCurrentUser":false,"pageCount":59,"score":0,"slideshowId":"288006715","sourceName":"LATEST","strippedTitle":"tkr-total-knee-replacement-surgery-of-the-century-dr-mohamed-ashraf-alleppey-pptx","type":"presentation","thumbnail":"https://cdn.slidesharecdn.com/ss_thumbnails/tkrtotalkneereplacement-surgeryofthecenturydrmohamedashrafalleppey-260611061151-d590da24-thumbnail.jpg?width=640\u0026height=640\u0026fit=bounds","description":"total knee replacement is becoming one of the most successful surgical procedures in the history of mankind.it alleviates the disability and sufferings of millions ofpeople worldwide.\nit has surpassed total hip replacement as the surgery of the century in terms of volume and outcome.\nthis surgical procedure is still under evolution due to the introduction of various types of implants and newer technology like robotic tkr where safety and precision meet togive optimum best outcome to the patient.\nauthor DR MOHAMED ASHRAF is a well known academician and surgeon from the southern state of KERALA in india .\nhe is at present working as PROFESSOR AND HOD OF ORTHOPAEDICS AT TRAVANCORE MEDICAL COLLEGE AND MEDICITY HOSPITALS , KOLLAM , KERALA ,A TERTIARY CARE POST GRADUATE TEACHING HOSPITAL.\nHE WAS THE FORMER PROF AND HOD AT GOVT  TD MEDICAL COLLEGE HOSPITAL, ALLEPPEY KERALA ","tags":["osteoarthritis knee oa knee","surgery of the century","